# Scenario 2: Update Reading Status
# User Story: As a reader, I want to update my reading progress

### 1. Start reading "The Hobbit" (change status from want_to_read to reading)
PATCH http://localhost:8080/api/books/1/
Authorization: Token YOUR_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reading_status": "reading"
}

### Expected Response:
# {
#   "id": 1,
#   "title": "The Hobbit",
#   "author": {...},
#   "reading_status": "reading",
#   "date_started": "2025-09-25T11:00:00Z",  // Auto-set when status changes to reading
#   "date_finished": null,
#   ...
# }

### 2. Verify status change
GET http://localhost:8080/api/books/1/
Authorization: Token YOUR_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

### 3. Check books by reading status
GET http://localhost:8080/api/books/by_status/?status=reading
Authorization: Token YOUR_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

### 4. Finish reading the book
PATCH http://localhost:8080/api/books/1/
Authorization: Token YOUR_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reading_status": "finished"
}

### Expected Response:
# {
#   "id": 1,
#   "reading_status": "finished",
#   "date_finished": "2025-09-25T15:30:00Z",  // Auto-set when status changes to finished
#   ...
# }